This album was created by the playful dance duo Duck Sauce. Made up of two members, A-Trak and Armand Van Helden, Duck Sauce has been famous for around five years and going! Their first single was a song named aNYway which topped the charts at number 1 on the UK Dance charts in 2009. They have, since then, released a song called "Barbara Streisand" which hit number 1 in Austria, Belgium, Norway, Switzerland, the UK, and the United States.

Duck Sauce has been working on their album "Quack" for five whole years and finally released it in 2014. The songs all have samples which take a long time to get approved for use in their albums. Songs, like "NRG", "It's You" are just a few of the amazing and hip moving tracks that cover this album all over! After every song, there is audio which is comedic and entertaining and also serves to keep the listener in a sort of fun and smiley mood.

Great job, Duck Sauce, for finishing your first album!

I hope you all love it!
